Assess model fit

In the full dataset, the correlation between the models value estimates and actual value estimates from participants task experience: mean = 0.42 SD = 0.34

Compute asymmetry index

Asymmetry index: Mean = -0.08 SD = 0.37

Identify participants with good vs.subpar model fit

Number of participants total (regardless of fit) = 383

Number of participants with correlation lower that 0 or negative loglikelihood less than 0 (i.e., poorly fit by the model) = 78

Number of participants with adequate model fit = 305

Analyses with participants with good model fit (main text analysis)

In the subset of data with good RL model fit, the correlation between the models value estimates and actual value estimates from participants task experience: mean = 0.54 SD = 0.22

Clean up good fit dataset

Plot parameter distributions
